If you make an SGI as cheap as a PC, you'll have a PC.
 
>    There are bilions people around the glob seeing/reading/wanting to get
>    a start at the wonder of 3D/VR, you don't care much about them, do you?

That many? Wow! And it's such a small "glob" too. So, you mean to say, that 
by advocating affordable 3D software, that I don't care? Opposed to your 
advocacy of SGI/Wavefront which is supposed to make 3D available to the 
thousands rather than the millions (or as you would, milions).
> 
>    Thanks to ViewTek/Impulse/CBM/DPS and others, that give a chance to start,
>    to people that don't need to sell their house in order to have a studio.
>
I'm not sure you caught my drift....
 
