@node IML-104 " MSG-104  Subject: New "Trans_mod" texture
@toc contents

Subject: New "Trans_mod" texture
Date:    Thursday, 10 November 1994 00:43:45 
From:    Patrick Sauvageau <sauvp@citi.doc.ca>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


This is a texture a have written for a friend who wanted to apply a
brushmap label on a transparent bottle. Normally, the filter setting of the
bottle will make the label as transparent as the rest bottle. With this
texture, you may specify a single color to have another filter setting.
So you may crete a green (0,150,60) bottle, with filter value set to 0,0,0.
Apply a brush as the label, then the texture. In the texture, you will specify t
hat
you want the color "Green (0,150,60)" to have ( 100,255,200) as it's filter
value. The only restriction is that you canot have this exact color on your
brush, unless you want this part to become transparent.



