Subject: Re: TIF -> AVI?? MPEG???
Date:    Saturday, 19 November 1994 05:26:33 
From:    taycock@kestrel.cqi.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


I have had some luck using Imagine 2.0 rendered Targas and OS/2's AVI 
Utility, this comes with WARP in the bonus pack.  Since WARP is so new I 
can't guarentee how or if this process works like it should bu I was able 
to get this to work.  It was tricky though and I can't tell you how to 
make it work everytime it was a little iffy, but thats life on the 
bleeding edge.

In case you are getting your hopes up I could NOT get Imagine 2.0 to run 
in a dos session under OS/2.  I had to boot in DOS to render and then 
reboot in OS/2 to make the files.  This may be more of a hassle than it's 
worth.

Good luck and let me know if you do find something that works well.


