@node IML-209 " MSG-209  Subject: Re: Amiga-PC connection
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Amiga-PC connection
Date:    Tuesday, 22 November 1994 03:49:06 
From:    Kent Marshall Worley <mumu@america.net>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  




On Fri, 28 Oct 1994, Nikola Vukovljak wrote:

> There is something like Parnet (or at least it uses the Parallel port) to 
> connect between Amiga and PC. In fact you can also use it to connect 2 
> Amigas or 2 PC's.
> 
> It is a commercial package (Cable + software) made by Legendary Design 
> Technologies in Canada.
> 
> The cost is pretty good though (US$ 59.95) so I've just ordered one.
> The software on the PC runs through Windows, and on the Amiga - via WB.
> 
> If anyone is interested as to how well this works E-mail me in about 2 
> weeks (after I get it and use it) and I'll let you know.
