@node IML-244 " MSG-244  Subject: Best PC Paint Program
@toc contents

Subject: Best PC Paint Program
Date:    Wednesday, 23 November 1994 23:57:29 
From:    cwhite@rmii.com (Curtis White)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


A very nice paint/image manipulation program is called Fauve Matisse.  You can g
et
it for $99 and it has many nice features.  It has tons of filters to do blurs, 
mosaic, tone correction, etc.  You can float selections as separate objects and 
work
on just that object or use it as a mask.  It has all kinds of different brushes,
 like
paint brushes, pencil, stamps, etc.  It can do many different paper textures and
 you
can define your own textures that you can apply to the image.  It can use Kai's
Power Tools plug-ins as well as most other Photoshop plug-ins.  Overall, it is a
n
excellent program.  It is comparable to Fractal Design Painter for about 1/3 the

cost.  If you want more details on what it can do, let me know.  It also can rea
d
and write almost any image format.  Hope this helps!




