On Thu, 24 Nov 1994, Dave Nagy wrote:

> If I were doing this, (if I weren't so lazy) I would start with a 
> ridiculously low value (like 0.00) and work up...  If Impulse has misplaced 
> a decimal somewhere, 1.52 may well be something like .0152 or .152 now...
 
Good idea, but Imagine only allows values between 1.00 and 3.50.
 
> 
> Don't put yourself out.  I think most folks would rather take your word 
for > it rather than DL-ing a bunch of pics.
> 

Too late. :)  I just ran 2.9 and 3.0 at the same time and rendered 14 pics.
7 of a tumbler with IOR's from 1.01-1.5 and 7 of a wine glass, same deal.
The results are quite interesting.  3.0's pics don't even resemble 2.9's.

I believe Impulse rewrote the routine for this reason:

      There are NO black areas in the glass in 3.0 where in 2.9 it's
      full of black areas.  This is with RSDP=16 (highest allowed) in
      BOTH versions.

So, they fixed it and broke it at the same time.  What else is new. ;)

I won't upload the pics unless someone wants them.  They're only HAM6
160x100.  Guess I'll be callin' Impulse.

Nick

      


