From:    Ed Totman <etotman@gort.ucsd.edu>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


On Mon, 28 Nov 1994, Douglas Rudd wrote:
> The results were as follows:
> 
>     A1200/030-50mhz: 14 hours apx
>     486DX2/50:       9:40 hours apx
>     A2000/040-33mhz: 5:20 hours apx
> 
> 
> As I said, this is only one data point. Many variable could enter, but
> for me, my 040 is consistantly faster than either my 030 or 486. I 

Although I don't want this thread to degenerate into an Amiga/PC war, I 
feel I must make the point that one can obtain an entire 486/66 system 
for less than $1000.  A new 040 system would cost at least 2x as much.
I own both Amiga's and PC's, so I know the benefits of both platforms, but 
cost is a major factor for most people.

Ed Totman
