On Mon, 28 Nov 1994, Andrew Conway wrote:

> Dear Folks,
>     I'm beginning to feel that my A3000's 030/25 is simply not enough for
> ray-tracing in Imagine. Does Imagine take the 68040 to its full worth-
> how many times faster in *practice* is it than the 030?
> 
>  I'm wondering if folk could tell me about their experiences
> (good/bad) in putting an 040 accelerator in an A3000. I'm especially
> concerned with contiguous memory problems in playing anims.
> thanks
> Andrew
> 
 I have had problems with a GVP 68040 accelerator and ADPRO and OPALVISION.
large 24bit picture files or anims would not load. It has been a while, I 
cannot remember the error but it never worked and I started using a PC to 
render and transfer the images to the Amiga. This was an A3000T and it 
was over a year ago and I think 68040 hardware has gotten better. 
   Kent Worley


